-- Schalke Ties Bayern Atop Bundesliga; Juventus Increases Lead
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-01-21T22:19:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-21/schalke-ties-bayern-atop-bundesliga-juventus-increases-lead.html
Schalke beat Stuttgart 3-1 to tie
 Bayern Munich  for the lead in German soccer’s Bundesliga.  Schalke and Bayern, which lost last night 3-1 to
Monchengladbach, have 37 points. Dortmund is three points back
and can pull even by winning at Hamburg tomorrow.  Juventus beat Atalanta 2-0 to increase its lead in Italy’s
Serie A to four points over defending champion AC Milan, while
Roma beat Cessena 5-1.  Francesco Totti  scored twice to give him
221 goals for Roma, breaking former AC Milan striker Gunnar
Nordahl’s record for most goals with a single club in Italy.  Celtic beat St. Mirren 2-0 to move four points ahead in the
Scottish Premier League over Rangers, which tied Aberdeen 1-1.
Celtic has won 12 straight league matches.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
